# Roadmap

Last updated: April 26, 2026.

This roadmap tracks current product and security priorities. `docs/audit.md` is still the detailed source of truth; this file is the short operational map.

## Phase A: Privacy And Data Lifecycle
- Landed baseline: support warnings, server-side sensitive-content rejection, lifecycle columns, hashed route logs, clear-all local data, sign-out cleanup, Settings privacy copy, and planning import/export guardrails.
- Remaining: local autosave setting, support retention/deletion execution, admin triage workflow, and a final cloud-sync policy for planning teacher notes.
- Keep user-facing privacy copy precise: "never stored" applies specifically to drafting raw notes and generated AI output, with explicit planning/support exceptions.

## Phase B: Support And Operations
- Landed baseline: server-side `app_admins` allowlist, `/admin/support` queue, status filters, assignment, redaction, soft deletion, and support operations runbook.
- Keep raw support emails out of route logs; use request IDs, user IDs, hashes, or aggregate counters.
- Configure and test `OPS_ALERT_WEBHOOK_URL` in deployed environments.
- Remaining: deployed alert validation, support retention automation, support notification delivery, abuse dashboard, and runbooks for AI provider failures, planning sync conflicts, account deletion, and release rollback.

## Phase C: Planning Sync Reliability
- Replace timestamp-only conflict detection with server-generated revisions and conditional writes.
- Make `updated_at` server-owned and store client edit timestamps separately.
- Add conflict history/audit rows and tests for stale queue replay, duplicate flushes, offline/online races, and multi-device edits.
- Keep product copy honest until this becomes revisioned sync: best-effort backup/sync, not collaboration-grade sync.

## Phase D: AI Quality And Safety
- Version prompts/models in usage metadata.
- Add a golden eval and red-team suite for Swedish school documentation, placeholder preservation, and hallucination resistance.
- Add post-generation suspicious-output checks or warnings before copy/export.
- Add provider timeout/cancel handling and a live AI smoke test with synthetic scrubbed input.

## Phase E: Account And Security Maturity
- Add email change, account deletion, data export, and session/security settings.
- Decide whether registration should hide account-existence signals.
- Add app-level auth throttling if Supabase platform controls are not sufficient.
- Harden CSP through report-only rollout, then nonce/hash enforcement where feasible.
- Complete manual accessibility and live auth-security sign-off.

## Phase F: Product Expansion
- Expand curriculum coverage and planning depth only after privacy, support, sync, and AI governance work lands.
- Revisit OCR/handwritten-note import after the privacy and evaluation harness exists.
- Add new templates based on real support/feedback patterns, not speculative scope.
